HB Draft 2026 Regular Session
Abstract: Reconstitutes and reconfirms the board of commissioners membership within the
Southeast Louisiana Flood Protection Authority-East.
Present law specifies that the board of commissioners of the SE La. Flood Protection
Authority-East be composed of nine members, with specified members residing in certain
parishes within the state. Requires the members be appointed by the governor from
nominations submitted by the nominating committee under specific conditions.
Proposed law requires that, as of Aug. 1, 2026, the composition and membership of the SE
La. Flood Protection Authority-East be reconstituted and reconfirmed by the Senate.
Requires any member not confirmed be treated as an unexpected vacancy and the
nominating committee follow the procedures outlined in present law to fill the vacancy.
Specifies that any membership not reconfirmed expire immediately and not be reappointed
for a period of two years. Requires that members reconfirmed possess the same term
requirement as the original appointment and any successor complete the term applicable to
their predecessor.
(Adds R.S.38:330.1(C)(1)(a)(iv))
